// =============================================================================
// core/database/sqlite/native/l1_pager/mod.vr — Pager layer (Layer 1)
// =============================================================================
// Layer: 1 of the loom architecture (sqlite-native.md §4.2)
// Dependencies: l0_vfs, core/mem/arena (CBGR), core/sync/atomic
// =============================================================================
//
// The pager sits between the VFS (L0 — raw byte-addressable storage) and
// the B-tree (L3 — structured key/value storage). It owns the **page
// cache**, the **write-ahead log**, and the **rollback journal**; it is
// the sole component that turns on-disk byte patterns into in-memory
// page frames and back.
//
// Architecture (sqlite-native.md §4.3, §8):
//
//   * Single-writer actor — one task owns the pager mutably. Writes flow
//     through `PagerRequest` messages on a bounded `Mailbox`. Readers
//     use snapshot views over the WAL frame watermark and never take
//     mutable references.
//
//   * CBGR-arena page cache — pages are `ThinRef<PageFrame>` into an
//     `Arena`. A checkpoint bumps the arena generation, invalidating
//     every live reader in O(1) — no ref-counting, no GC sweep.
//
//   * Epoch-reclaimed frame recycling — freed frames are parked on an
//     epoch list and returned to the arena once the last reader who
//     could possibly still hold a reference has retired.
//
// This v0.1 module ships:
//
//   * `PageNo` refinement type (positive, < 2^31)
//   * `PageFrame` (byte-addressable page buffer with dirty flag)
//   * `Pager` — in-memory pager running on top of a MemDbFile. Actor
//     harness + checkpointer are Phase 1 step 2 deliverables.
//   * `PageCacheMap` — a thin LRU over PageNo → PageFrame for the
//     in-memory pager. The CBGR-backed arena cache lands with the
//     actor harness.
//
// Deliberately NOT shipped in v0.1 (per spec §25.2):
//
//   * WAL / rollback journal — Phase 1 step 3
//   * Checkpointer — Phase 1 step 3
//   * Supervisor integration — Phase 1 step 4
//   * PosixVfs-backed Pager — blocked on stdlib Windows-parity sweep
//     and the two language issues logged as #6 / #7.
//
// =============================================================================

module core.database.sqlite.native.l1_pager;

public module pager;

public mount .pager.{
    PageNo, PageFrame, Pager, PagerError, PagerErrorKind,
    PAGE_SIZE_MIN, PAGE_SIZE_MAX, PAGE_SIZE_DEFAULT,
    pager_open_memory, pager_read, pager_write, pager_close,
};
